The paper deals with an online optimization problem involving a stream of data and limited buffer capacity, which is a classic topic in computer science. The problem is related to scheduling and decision-making, which are central topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves statistical analysis and probability theory, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper introduces a new measure of input density, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
